    • Constructor Detail

      • CompoundOrder

        public CompoundOrder(RowOrder[] orders)
        Creates a new instance with the given array of RowOrders. The precedence of the orderings is from front to back (first to last index in the array).
        Parameters:
        orders - non-null array of row orders of length > 0. On return, you can do whatever with array: a defensive copy is maintained by this instance.

    • Method Detail

      • compareRows

        public int compareRows(ByteBuffer rowA,
              ByteBuffer rowB)
        Description copied from class: RowOrder
        Compares two rows. The two rows are assumed to be non null. This is a read-only operation: the implementation shall not ever modify the state of its input arguments; modifying then restoring the position and limits is not permissible.

        Note, one of the input arguments may be a key, in which case the implementation may allow the key to have a different length than the row.

        Specified by:
        compareRows in class RowOrder
        Returns:
        the return value has the same semantics as Comparator.compare(Object, Object)
